    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>1 cup lukewarm milk</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons sugar</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon active dry yeast</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1/2 cup brown sugar</li>
            <li>1/2 cup chopped mixed nuts (e.g., peanuts, walnuts)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup chopped dried fruit (e.g., raisins)</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil for frying</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Hoddeok</li>
            <li>Korean</li>
            <li>Dessert</li>
            <li>Fried</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, combine lukewarm milk and sugar. Stir until the sugar is dissolved. Sprinkle active dry yeast over the mixture and let it sit for about 5 minutes, or until foamy.</li>
            <li>In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and salt. Make a well in the center and pour in the yeast mixture. Mix until a dough forms.</li>
            <li>Knead the dough on a floured surface until it becomes smooth and elastic. Place the dough in a greased bowl, cover it with a damp cloth, and let it rise in a warm place for about 1 hour, or until doubled in size.</li>
            <li>While the dough is rising, mix brown sugar, chopped nuts, dried fruit, and ground cinnamon in a bowl. Set aside.</li>
            <li>Punch down the risen dough and divide it into small balls. Flatten each ball and place a spoonful of the sugar-nut mixture in the center. Seal the edges and form into a smooth ball again.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat. Fry the hoddeok until both sides are golden brown and crispy.</li>
            <li>Remove from the pan and drain on paper towels. Serve Hoddeok warm.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Hoddeok!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

